Johannesburg- The new year has brought about change, not only in people’s lives, but in the entertainment industry as well. This comes after Generations the Legacy introduced its new intro song in last night’s episode. The show has not only introduced new faces, a different storyline, and fresh content, it has also changed its opening sequence as well. Die-hard fans of the SABC1’s daily soapie, have since shown love to the new song, saying change is rather good, while some say they thought they were watching a totally different show. Take a look at what some of them had to say on Twitter below:  See tweeps react to the new intro song for the show:         For the latest entertainment news from Sunday World, click here. Or read the latest from Shwashwi here. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. 